#CircuitBreakerSG D-43

Dinner tonight is some old favourites. Orange Pork Ribs that we haven't had for a while & the almost weekly blanched Baby Kailan.

Lastly some Bak Kwa that was delivered this afternoon. Can't believe that we actually have it as a dish 😅

Enjoy your #dinner too!
.

I must say your orange pork ribs really caught my attention. An interesting yet refreshing dish 👍 @yvonnemsw
@sooleng_ng Usually we buy Bak Kwa during CNY only. Dunno why now 😅
Love your all time orange pork ribs! And yesss..i bought bak kwa today too😍
Look at those beautiful baby Gai Lan! I miss them so much!😋
@goodfoodandgreatbooks Thanks Irene. Love your vibrant breakfast always 😍
Always beautiful, yummy and healthy meals!💚
@baking_with_double_grace Thanks for your kind words, Grace. Simple homecooked 😍
@yvonnemsw I m so exhausted the minute I finished cooking, no more energy to dress up my dishes. Yours r always a joy to look at!
How did u manage to cook so delicious n pretty looking food everyday? ❤️❤️❤️ You r a v good cook!
@jane_wu Thanks Jane 😍  This appears every few months 😆
@yvonnemsw so many dishes in my to cook list,how to catch up 🤣
@tet_chu Send my the list, I dunno what to cook 😆
@yvonnemsw my list keeps increasing because you cooked to o many dishes that I wanna cook 🤣
Pork ribs look so darn good! 😍
Omg of my absolutely favourite is your orange chicken ❤️
@vnm_lee We also like to kiap loti with it 🙌😋👍
We had Orange Chicken last night! 😁Bak Kwa is so good with anything..love it best with some white bread!! 😍
